        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 5:33PM PDT by NWS Sacramento CA</headline>
        <description>At 532 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of Pinecrest, or 21 miles southwest of Sonora Pass,
moving west at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Long Barn.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
